or expired. Please reconnect your GitHub account."}],"isError":true},"status":"completed","startTime":1771625074300,"endTime":1771625079834,"duration":5534,"timestamp":"2026-02-20T22:04:39.834Z"},{"id":"toolu_bdrk_019atWWTRE6gCaypQceREYmV","name":"get_workflow_runs","tool":"get_workflow_runs","toolName":"get_workflow_runs","serverId":"openagentic_github","serverName":"openagentic_github","executedOn":"mcp-proxy","arguments":{"owner":"openagentic","repo":"openagentic","per_page":10},"result":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Error calling tool 'get_workflow_runs': GitHub token is invalid or expired. Please reconnect your GitHub account."}],"isError":true},"status":"completed","startTime":1771625074300,"endTime":1771625079834,"duration":5534,"timestamp":"2026-02-20T22:04:39.834Z"},{"id":"toolu_bdrk_01X8WsiCyFvjHMSyV7Pkuf9i","name":"web_search","tool":"web_search","toolName":"web_search","serverId":"openagentic_web","serverName":"openagentic_web","executedOn":"mcp-proxy","arguments":{"query":"OpenAgentic GitHub repository openagentic","num_results":10},"result":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"success\":true,\"query\":\"OpenAgentic GitHub repository openagentic\",\"num_results\":10,\"results\":[{\"title\":\"Automate repository tasks with GitHub Agentic Workflows\",\"url\":\"https://github.blog/ai-and-ml/automate-repository-tasks-with-github-agentic-workflows/\",\"snippet\":\"GitHubAgentic Workflows use coding agents at runtime, which incur billing costs. When using Copilot with default settings, each workflow run typically incurs two premium requests: one for theopenagenticand one for a guardrail check through safe outputs. The models used can be configured to help manage these costs.\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub Agentic Workflows Unleash AI-Driven Repository Automation\",\"url\":\"https://www.infoq.com/news/2026/02/github-agentic-workflows/\",\"snippet\":\"Recently launched in technical preview,GitHubAgentic Workflows introduce a way to automate complex, repetitiverepositorytasks using coding agents that understand context and intent,GitHub...\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub Agentic Workflows: The Future of Repository Automation\",\"url\":\"https://www.webnuz.com/article/2026-02-19/GitHub%20Agentic%20Workflows%3A%20The%20Future%20of%20Repository%20Automation\",\"snippet\":\"GitHubAgentic Workflows represent a fundamental shift: from \\\"code your automation\\\" to \\\"describe your automation.\\\" The AI handles translation. This is not replacing developers. It is giving us better tools to offload the tedious, repetitive parts ofrepositorymaintenance so we can focus on actually building things. Will there be growing pains?\"},{\"title\":\"Awesome Agentic Workflow Repository - GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/irfanfadhullah/Awesome-Agentic-Workflow\",\"snippet\":\"A curated collection ofGitHubrepositories focused on agentic workflows, autonomous agents, multi-agent systems, and AI workflow automation. Thisrepositoryserves as a comprehensive resource hub containing summarized documentation from projects related to intelligent agent frameworks and automated workflow orchestration.\"},{\"title\":\"With Agentic Workflows, GitHub wants to help automate repo maintenance\",\"url\":\"https://tessl.io/blog/with-agentic-workflows-github-wants-to-help-automate-repo-maintenance/\",\"snippet\":\"\\\"The use ofGitHubAgentic Workflows makes entirely new categories ofrepositoryautomation and software engineering possible, in a way that fits naturally with how developer teams already work onGitHub,\\\"GitHubwrote in a blog post. One exampleGitHubprovides is a daily issues report workflow.\"},{\"title\":\"Agentic Workflows - GitHub Next\",\"url\":\"https://githubnext.com/projects/agentic-workflows/\",\"snippet\":\"Software collaboration keeps evolving. With Continuous AI,GitHubNext are exploring how LLMs can help teams with documentation, quality, triage, and more. Agentic Workflows is a follow‑up exploration: a research demonstrator focused on expressing repository‑level behaviors in natural language and running them onGitHub.\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub Agentic Workflows Bring AI Agents to Actions - Ken Muse\",\"url\":\"https://www.kenmuse.com/blog/github-agentic-workflows-bring-ai-agents-to-actions/\",\"snippet\":\"ExploreGitHub'snew Agentic Workflows -- AI coding agents inGitHubActions with defense-in-depth security and natural language automation.\"},{\"title\":\"Building and Running Agentic Workflows: A New Era of Automation on GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/@mvpkenlin/building-and-running-agentic-workflows-a-new-era-of-automation-on-github-99b70916cc13\",\"snippet\":\"Automation onGitHubis evolving fast, and one of the most exciting shifts is the rise of agentic workflows — a model where AI agents execute natural‑language instructions directly inside ...\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub Tests AI Agents to Handle Repository Upkeep\",\"url\":\"https://devops.com/github-tests-ai-agents-to-handle-repository-upkeep/\",\"snippet\":\"GitHubsays each workflow executes within an isolated environment, with default permissions limiting the agent's ability to alterrepositorycontents directly. Suggested edits are set for approval rather than applied automatically. Network access is restricted, and outputs are filtered before being written back to the codebase.\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub Agentic Workflows: The Future of Repository Automation\",\"url\":\"https://dev.to/damogallagher/github-agentic-workflows-the-future-of-repository-automation-afl\",\"snippet\":\"Yesterday,GitHubofficially announced the technical preview ofGitHubAgentic Workflows — and this... Tagged withgithub, automation, ai, devops.\"}],\"source\":\"duckduckgo-html\",\"tip\":\"Use web_fetch to read the full content of any interesting result\"}"}],"structuredContent":{"success":true,"query":"OpenAgentic GitHub repository openagentic","num_results":10,"results":[{"title":"Automate repository tasks with GitHub Agentic Workflows","url":"https://github.blog/ai-and-ml/automate-repository-tasks-with-github-agentic-workflows/","snippet":"GitHubAgentic Workflows use coding agents at runtime, which incur billing costs. When using Copilot with default settings, each workflow run typically incurs two premium requests: one for theopenagenticand one for a guardrail check through safe outputs. The models used can be configured to help manage these costs."},{"title":"GitHub Agentic Workflows Unleash AI-Driven Repository Automation","url":"https://www.infoq.com/news/2026/02/github-agentic-workflows/","snippet":"Recently launched in technical preview,GitHubAgentic Workflows introduce a way to automate complex, repetitiverepositorytasks using coding agents that understand context and intent,GitHub..."},{"title":"GitHub Agentic Workflows: The Future of Repository Automation","url":"https://www.webnuz.com/article/2026-02-19/GitHub%20Agentic%20Workflows%3A%20The%20Future%20of%20Repository%20Automation","snippet":"GitHubAgentic Workflows represent a fundamental shift: from \"code your automation\" to \"describe your automation.\" The AI handles translation. This is not replacing developers. It is giving us better tools to offload the tedious, repetitive parts ofrepositorymaintenance so we can focus on actually building things. Will there be growing pains?"},{"title":"Awesome Agentic Workflow Repository - GitHub","url":"https://github.com/irfanfadhullah/Awesome-Agentic-Workflow","snippet":"A curated collection ofGitHubrepositories focused on agentic workflows, autonomous agents, multi-agent systems, and AI workflow automation. Thisrepositoryserves as a comprehensive resource hub containing summarized documentation from projects related to intelligent agent frameworks and automated workflow orchestration."},{"title":"With Agentic Workflows, GitHub wants to help automate repo maintenance","url":"https://tessl.io/blog/with-agentic-workflows-github-wants-to-help-automate-repo-maintenance/","snippet":"\"The use ofGitHubAgentic Workflows makes entirely new categories ofrepositoryautomation and software engineering possible, in a way that fits naturally with how developer teams already work onGitHub,\"GitHubwrote in a blog post. One exampleGitHubprovides is a daily issues report workflow."},{"title":"Agentic Workflows - GitHub Next","url":"https://githubnext.com/projects/agentic-workflows/","snippet":"Software collaboration keeps evolving. With Continuous AI,GitHubNext are exploring how LLMs can help teams with documentation, quality, triage, and more. Agentic Workflows is a follow‑up exploration: a research demonstrator focused on expressing repository‑level behaviors in natural language and running them onGitHub."},{"title":"GitHub Agentic Workflows Bring AI Agents to Actions - Ken Muse","url":"https://www.kenmuse.com/blog/github-agentic-workflows-bring-ai-agents-to-actions/","snippet":"ExploreGitHub'snew Agentic Workflows -- AI coding agents inGitHubActions with defense-in-depth security and natural language automation."},{"title":"Building and Running Agentic Workflows: A New Era of Automation on GitHub","url":"https://medium.com/@mvpkenlin/building-and-running-agentic-workflows-a-new-era-of-automation-on-github-99b70916cc13","snippet":"Automation onGitHubis evolving fast, and one of the most exciting shifts is the rise of agentic workflows — a model where AI agents execute natural‑language instructions directly inside ..."},{"title":"GitHub Tests AI Agents to Handle Repository Upkeep","url":"https://devops.com/github-tests-ai-agents-to-handle-repository-upkeep/","snippet":"GitHubsays each workflow executes within an isolated environment, with default permissions limiting the agent's ability to alterrepositorycontents directly. Suggested edits are set for approval rather than applied automatically. Network access is restricted, and outputs are filtered before being written back to the codebase."},{"title":"GitHub Agentic Workflows: The Future of Repository Automation","url":"https://dev.to/damogallagher/github-agentic-workflows-the-future-of-repository-automation-afl","snippet":"Yesterday,GitHubofficially announced the technical preview ofGitHubAgentic Workflows — and this... Tagged withgithub, automation, ai, devops."}],"source":"duckduckgo-html","tip":"Use web_fetch to read the full content of any interesting result"},"isError":false},"status":"completed","startTime":1771625074300,"endTime":1771625079834,"duration":5534,"timestamp":"2026-02-20T22:04:39.834Z"},{"id":"toolu_bdrk_01Jp2QT9FFKxiekfgicLWSJF","name":"flowise_get_auth_status","tool":"flowise_get_auth_status","toolName":"flowise_get_auth_status","serverId":"openagentic_flowise","serverName":"openagentic_flowise","executedOn":"mcp-proxy","arguments":{},"result":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1 validation error for call[flowise_get_auth_status]\nmeta\n  Unexpected keyword argument [type=unexpected_keyword_argument, input_value={'userAccessToken': 'eyJh... 'admin@openagentic.io'}, input_type=dict]\n    For further information visit https://errors.pydantic.dev/2.12/v/unexpected_keyword_argument"}],"isError":true},"status":"completed","startTime":1771625083161,"endTime":1771625083760,"duration":599,"timestamp":"2026-02-20T22:04:43.760Z"},{"id":"toolu_bdrk_01VvzMRLSb8z22oM5tdnq7NR","name":"search_code","tool":"search_code","toolName":"search_code","serverId":"openagentic-manager","serverName":"openagentic-manager","executedOn":"openagentic-api-6ffdf956b5-6gztf","arguments":{"query":"openagentic org:openagentic"},"result":null,"error":"Code execution failed: Failed to create code execution session","status":"failed","startTime":1771625083161,"endTime":1771625083760,"duration":599,"timestamp":"2026-02-20T22:04:43.760Z"}],"tokenUsage":{"prompt_tokens":0,"completion_tokens":2113,"total_tokens":2113},"model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","source":"database","confirmed":true,"final":true}

